args:
Jupiter begins his investigation immediately,
and the party is fired up when he finds some
seemingly effective evidence. But when the
sleazy prosecutor declares victory will still be
his, the dragon sets out to form a new plan.
Er, sorry. Could you repeat that?
I said, I will be your defense attorney!\nNo need for concern, dear clients;\nI have quite the silver tongue!
That's actually making me MORE worried.\nBut it's not like I have anyone else who's\nwilling to take the case, soooo...
Oh, fine! You're hired. But if you lose,\nyou're in BIG trouble, buster!
I wouldn't have it any other way.\nNow then, what can you tell me\nabout your case?
Okay, so a couple days ago, I had some\nerrands to run in the shopping district.
But on my way back, I wound up getting\nin trouble with some imperial goons...
Yo, my little lady! Come on over here!\nWe don't bite, we don't scratch,\nyou got nothing to fear!
Not on your life. Now make like my fist\nin your face and beat it.

Wassup with all the 'tude?
You're bein' really rude!
But if you think you'll pass by us,
then I'm afraid you're screwed!
Would you BACK OFF already?!\nUgh, fine. I'll just go around.
Blech! What was WITH those jerks?\nNow I have to walk down this creepy\ndark street...
Someone collapsed over there!\nH-hey! Are you okay?!
Oh no! There's a knife in his back!\nI think he's...he's...
Hey, you're the mayor's daughter, right?\nWhat are you...?
AAAAAH! MURDER! MURDER MOST FOUL!\nCALL THE GUARDS! CALL THE TEMPLARS!\nTHE MAYOR'S DAUGHTER IS A MURDERER!
Whoa, hey! Slow down! This poor guy\nwas already dead when I found him!
Oh yeah? Then why does the knife in his\nback have YOUR family crest on it?!
Huh? Wait a second...I know this knife!\nIt's the one some thief broke in and stole\nfrom me the other day!
It's the THIEF who did this, not me!\nHe's the one you want!
Yeah, like I'm gonna believe that.\nHALP! HAAAAAALP! MURRRRRDEEEEER!
...And that's how I found myself tossed\ninto the hoosegow.
Yes, I see. While I don't know exactly\nwhat transpired, I think I understand\nthe basic outline of the case.

I also learned that you're not exactly the
best liar in the world, which makes me
rather positive you are not, in fact,
the murderer.
Sure do. It's a lawyer's job to believe in\ntheir client 'til the very end, after all.
Well then, with that nugget in my pocket,\nit's time for me to do a little investigating\naround town.
Oh, and I'll be back this evening, so you\ntwo play nice while I'm gone. Toodles!
Y'know, despite the way he looks,\nhe's surprisingly nice.
Yeah, he can be a bit flighty, but he's the\nkind of friend you can always count on\nwhen push comes to shove.
A friend, huh? That's nice. It's always\ngood to have someone you can trust.
If my father had someone like that back\nin the day, maybe things would have\nturned out differently.
Do you mean back when they stripped him\nof his elected office?
Yeah, exactly. It was all really weird!\nFirst my father's closest confidants all quit,\nand then that prosecutor came around.
The jerk invented some totally baseless\nscandal to charge him with the moment\nhe had no one around to back him.
Before we knew it, Dad was found guilty\nand the prosecutor became the new mayor.
Do you think the prosecutor was\nresponsible for his people quitting?
I suspect so, yeah. For generations, my\nfamily has protected both the mayoral seat\nand our sacred treasure.

That nasty prosecutor wanted both of 'em,
which is why there's no low-down, rotten
scheme he won't use to make sure my
family's out of the way forever.
What IS that treasure, anyway? Why will\npeople go to such lengths to have it?
Honestly, I'm not sure. The story I always\nheard was that some legendary dragon\nhelped my ancestor and gave it to him.

Nobody knows what's inside it, but I don't
even care about that. For me, it's just a
beautiful box that's been handed down in
my family for ages.
We've been told not to open it unless we're\nreally in a bind, so I always assumed there\nwas something crazy powerful inside.
Well, I suppose all we can do now is wait\nfor Jupiter to finish his investigation.
I just hope that guy actually knows\nwhat the heck he's doing...
Hello, my lovely clients! Those imperials\nwere a real pain in the tuchus, but I still\nmanaged to dig up some solid evidence.

Oh, and I actually used the front door to
come in this time since I'm your lawyer
and all, so no need to worry about soldiers
storming into the place.
Wait, so you actually...did something?\nSomething good, I mean?
Sounds like someone doesn't trust me.\nThat hurts! I trust you as my client, so you\nshould have the same faith in me.
We believe in you, Jupiter. Now please\njust tell us what you found?
Right then! I dug up two pieces of quite\ninteresting evidence, the first in regards\nto the scene of the crime.
As it turns out, the only ones on that road\nat the time were Eryn, the dead man,\nand the witness.
From the sounds of it, imperials cleared\neveryone else out of the area before Eryn\neven arrived.
So we had imperial guards forcing her\ndown that path while keeping everyone\nelse at bay? Interesting.
Indeed it is! Now then, the other little\ntidbit I learned about was the murder\nweapon itself.
The knife with my family's crest?
The very same! Turns out it was recently\npurchased from a secondhand shop.
Wait, so the thief didn't keep it?
No indeedy! According to the shopkeep,\nthe knife was traded in to him shortly\nbefore this whole unpleasant incident.
Which means the REAL murderer is\nwhoever bought the knife after it was sold.
Right you are! Apparently they found a\nbuyer just one day before all of the\nstabby-stabby.

And it turns out that buyer looked veeery
similar to the man who reported you for
murder! Soooo...are we all starting to see
where I'm going with this?
You think the real murderer was that guy\nwho saw me and started yelling loud\nenough to wake the dead!
With this kind of evidence, the trial might\neven work out in our favor. I think things\nare really starting to look up!
Oh, I wouldn't be so certain.

My hold on this courtroom is absolute.
Oh, you may have snooped around and
learned this or that, but you still don't
have a snowball's chance of besting me.
Prosecutor Guaron! How dare you\nshow your face to me, you jerk!
Don't glare at me as if I were your\nnemesis, dear girl. I've come to HELP you.
I'm giving you one last chance to hand\nover the key to Alberius's treasure.
Do that, and I'll clear your name\nand release you this very day.

I have a similar offer for you, good sir.
If you provide me with just a smidgen of
your dragonblood, you will walk out of
this place a free man once more.
As a citizen of Alberia at heart, it pains me\nto think I might have to force a prince to\ndo my biddingeven if he is a traitor.

I suppose I should have seen this coming.
Normally I don't mind a little bit of heavy-
handed threatening to get a job done, but I
simply can't abide it in this instance.
What absolute nerve you have to interrupt\nmy speech, sir! Identify yourself!

I'm these people's attorneyand seeing
as I've been here this entire time, I'd say
you have far more nerve to be ignoring
one so handsome and rugged as moi.
But let us set that aside for now.\nMy clients have no interest in your sham\nof an offer because I am going to win.

We have evidence of Eryn's innocence,
which means all I need to do is launch my
exceedingly clever plan to drag the true
culprit out of hiding.
Now, Mr. Guaranteed Prosecutor or\nwhatever name you go by: Are you still\nfeeling as puffed up as before?
Hmph! It seems your slick solicitor has\nsome bite! Well, that won't last.

Hear me well: My hold on the court in this
town is absolute, which means I am
absolute. And tomorrow, the treasure will
be mineand be mine absolutely!
And when that moment comes, you will\nrue the day you ever dared to defy me!
Huh. I actually thought he'd be more\nimpressed by me, but he doesn't seem\nnervous at all.

His negotiations failed, he knows I've
turned up all kinds of dirt, and yet he's
not upset at all! He must be very confident
in a courtroom victory tomorrow.

He'll just use his imperial soldiers to ruin
the whole thing like he always does.
That scumbucket will do anything to win,
and I mean A-NY-THING.
Well, I suppose it'd be best for us to do\nsome extra preparation juuuuust in case.
But how much more can we do?

What's the saying? It takes a troublemaker
to know a troublemaker or...something?
Point is, if he's going to play dirty,
we might as well get down in the mud.
Worry not, my fine clients! I'm off to take\ncare of a couple of things and ensure that\nwe win the day tomorrow!
I'll see you both in court. Toodles!
He actually just skipped out of here...\nI sure wish I shared his confidence!
